data.description: Listed with Connie Hicks, Coldwell Banker  Matheny Real Estate. Contact her if interested at 828-289-6102. Move-in ready, 1-level, spacious, bright and airy mid-century modern ranch house nestled in 4 wooded hillside acres overlooking Puzzle Creek and farmland. Next to Eastwood Village and Fair Haven Rest Home near East High School and Forest City. Including porches and 2-car attached carport, 2,800 sf under roof and almost 2,000  sf heated. Easily adaptable for handicapped use. Wonderful, cozy family home. Built by current owner's parents in 1955 with 1970s addition and many recent updates. Spacious living/dIning combination with fireplace, plus large den with vaulted ceiling and built-in bookcases. Three bedrooms. Lots of windows and light, beautiful views. Refinished wood floors throughout plus new den carpet and kitchen laminate. Updated baths. Lots of storage. HVAC heat pump new 2007. Roof new 2009. Forest City water. Extensive landscaping, flowerbeds, flowering shrubs, with ample space for a garden and additional buildings or another home site. Call for more details or to see this lovely home by appointment. Serious inquiries only.
data.whatILove: This home is a hillside oasis surrounded by beautiful mature trees on 4 acres...but just a quick 5-10 minute drive to stores and restaurants in one of North Carolina's prettiest small towns -- Forest City. Also close to the new Facebook facilly, 15 minutes to Rutherfordton, 30 to Shelby, 1 hr to Charlotte or Asheville. Perfect family or retirement home in the Blue Ridge Foothills.
